# Frontend Rules

> Goal: Write frontend code that a backend engineer can understand and review.

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 15 (App Router), TypeScript strict mode, Tailwind CSS v4, shadcn/ui
- Data fetching: TanStack Query (React Query)
- Forms: react-hook-form + zod validation
- State: React context / zustand (only if needed)

## Project Structure
```
frontend/
├── src/
│   ├── app/                  # Next.js App Router pages
│   │   ├── layout.tsx
│   │   ├── page.tsx
│   │   └── (auth)/
│   │       └── login/page.tsx
│   ├── components/
│   │   ├── ui/               # shadcn/ui components (auto-generated)
│   │   └── [feature]/        # feature-specific components
│   ├── lib/
│   │   ├── api.ts            # API client (fetch wrapper)
│   │   ├── api-types.ts      # AUTO-GENERATED from OpenAPI — DO NOT EDIT
│   │   └── utils.ts
│   ├── hooks/                # Custom React hooks
│   ├── styles/
│   │   └── globals.css
│   └── types/                # App-level type definitions
├── public/
├── package.json
└── tsconfig.json
```

## Component Documentation (IMPORTANT)
Every component file MUST have a header comment:
```typescript
/**
 * UserProfile - 用户资料展示组件
 *
 * 功能：展示用户基本信息，支持编辑和保存
 * 数据流：从父组件接收 userId → 调用 /api/users/:id → 展示数据
 * 交互：点击编辑 → 编辑模式 → 保存 → 触发 onUpdate 回调
 */
```
For complex features, add a data flow summary:
```
数据流：用户输入 → formData → handleSave() → API → 更新 state → onUpdate()
```

## Component Structure Order
Every component follows this order:
1. Props type definition
2. Component header comment (as above)
3. State declarations (with purpose comments)
4. API calls / data fetching
5. Side effects (`useEffect`)
6. Event handlers (prefix with `handle`)
7. Helper functions
8. Render logic

## State Annotations
Always annotate the purpose and source of state:
```typescript
const [isOpen, setIsOpen] = useState(false);              // UI state: dialog visibility
const { data: user } = useQuery(["user", id], fetchUser); // Server state: from /api/users/:id
const [formData, setFormData] = useState(initialValues);   // Form state: temp editing data
```

## Coding Conventions
- All components: functional + hooks, no class components
- Named exports only (no `export default` except page files)
- Co-locate component + types + tests in same directory
- Use `"use client"` only when client interactivity is needed
- Components under 200 lines; extract hooks/utils if longer
- Event handler naming: `handleXxx` (e.g. `handleSave`, `handleDelete`)

## Styling
- Tailwind CSS only — no CSS modules, no styled-components, no inline styles
- Use shadcn/ui as base; customize via Tailwind classes
- Color scheme: CSS variables in globals.css
- Responsive: mobile-first (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`)
- Implement accessibility (ARIA labels, keyboard navigation)

## Data Fetching
- ALL API calls go through `lib/api.ts`
- Use types from `lib/api-types.ts` (auto-generated, never hand-edit)
- Server components fetch directly; client components use TanStack Query
- Show loading (skeleton) and error states for all async operations

## Forms & Validation
- Zod schemas mirroring backend Pydantic models
- react-hook-form for form state management
- Inline validation errors next to each field
- Type-safe form data handling

## Performance
- Use `next/image` for all images
- Lazy load heavy components with `dynamic()` or `React.lazy()`
- Minimize `"use client"` — keep as much on server as possible
- Explain WHY when using `memo` / `useMemo` / `useCallback`
- Large lists: use virtual scrolling

## Business Logic Comments
Mark non-obvious business rules explicitly:
```typescript
// 业务规则：只有管理员可以删除用户
if (currentUser.role !== "admin") return;
```
Explain non-obvious design decisions:
```typescript
// 使用 debounce 防止搜索 API 被频繁调用（每次按键都会触发）
const debouncedSearch = useMemo(() => debounce(handleSearch, 300), []);
```

## Self-Review Checklist (run after completing a component)
Agent must be able to answer these 8 questions:
1. 这个组件的业务功能是什么？（文件头注释）
2. 用户如何与它交互？（事件处理函数）
3. 调用了哪些 API？（lib/api.ts）
4. 数据从哪来，到哪去？（状态标注）
5. 有没有错误处理？（try-catch / error boundary）
6. 类型定义是否完整？（禁止 any）
7. 有没有性能问题？（不必要的重渲染）
8. 是否符合业务规则？（权限、边界条件）

## DO NOT
- Manually write types that exist in `api-types.ts`
- Install new UI libraries without asking (shadcn/ui covers most needs)
- Use `any` — use `unknown` + type narrowing if truly unknown
- Leave unused imports
